<br>
Assistin... ifn m'go pull an m'targets one buh nudder goes an whacks me ya get da second one dat whacks me. Sometimes odder melee say ya when go switch targets... course m'didn buh who me ta say. So when assistin bes advice give is ta waits lil bit. Likes someone say... wait till ya see melee swingin. <br>
<br>
Did ya all know ya pets are vera fat?! Dey keeps mes from gettin close ta critta ta hit! Dat nudder benifit waiting fer melee ta engage critta afore sending pet in.<br>
<br>
Positionin o'da pet. One thin dat bug me is da pet being in mes taggin sight. Again fat pet.<br>
<br>
Now nudder thin bout sending pet in dat bug heck outta me as warrior is sometimes mes need ta stop a critta coming in an den pull it where m'wan to fight it. Pets will stop a critta in it's track an sometimes will cause extra crittas ta aggro on dem. Dis nudder reason good fer waitin ta send pet in.<br>
<br>
Hokies dems mes thoughts on da magie pets. Hope dey helpful!<br>
<br>
OOC: Sorry, I mostly do all posts in character no matter where I post. I have a 47 mage, which I usually solo.  I went to the Hole as my mage as my first dungeon expierence. Knowing what bothered me as a warrior allowed me to control my pet and always stay on target when sending it in. My pet and I survived until the end. *smiles* I find my mage very challenging tatically, and will continue to play her after my warrior gets to 60 (in a bout three levels). <br>
